Showers around early, though I don't expect any of that is heavy enough to stop play. Of greater interest is the potential for storms to fire this afternoon, and those WILL be heavy enough to be game-enders. If it pops on the ballpark, that's a game that ends before 9... if they just miss, the game plays fine. So, there's some definite risk (even with the earlier start time), really only like it for GPP's.
Low chance of a stray shower or sprinkle, no issues.
Some light off and on showers, they can play through it.
Scattered showers and storms, definitely a chance for a delay. Can't 100% rule out a PPD, but that would take some pretty bad pop-up storm luck, and it's quite unlikely, so I'm keeping this as YLW.
